    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's... that's a really dark way to put it. But honestly, it feels true. It feels like I've been running a marathon for years only to realize I wasn't even on a track, just running in circles in the dark. Everything I am is tied to this work, and now that it's gone, there's nothing left. I just want the noise to stop. I just want to be able to rest without feeling this constant, gnawing pressure to be something I'm not.",
